question: Please provide names of the patients that are linked with the organization ROYAL OF FAIRHAVEN NURSING CENTER.
answers:
```sql
SELECT
```
```sql
  p.first,
  p.last
```
```sql
FROM patients AS p

  ON p.id = e.patient
```

```sql
WHERE

```

question: What is the quality of the supply with the code 463659001?
answers:
```sql
WITH Description_Temp AS (
  SELECT
    s.code,
    s.description,
    p.first,
    p.last
  FROM supplies AS s
  JOIN patients AS p
    ON p.id = s.patient
  JOIN encounters AS e
    ON e.id = s.encounter
  WHERE
    p.first = 'OLIVER' AND p.last = 'JENSEN' AND s.code = 463659001
), Rating_Temp AS (
  SELECT
    o.name AS org,
    AVG(q.rating) AS avg_rating
  FROM organizations AS o
  JOIN providers AS p
    ON p.organization = o.id
  JOIN encounters AS e
    ON e.provider = p.id
  JOIN patients AS pa
    ON pa.id = e.patient
  JOIN description_temp AS dt
    ON dt.code = e.code
  JOIN ratings AS q
    ON q.provider = p.id
  GROUP BY
    o.name
)
SELECT
  dt.description,
  dt.code,
  rt.org,
  rt.avg_rating
FROM description_temp AS dt
JOIN rating_temp AS rt
  ON rt.org = 'University of Pennsylvania Health System';
```

question: What are the typical symptoms of the allergy described as Shellfish (substance)?
answers:
```sql
SELECT
  DISTINCT
  CASE
    WHEN a.reaction1 = 114861
    THEN t1.description
    WHEN a.reaction1 = 158053
    THEN t2.description
    WHEN a.reaction1 = 581679
    THEN t3.description
    WHEN a.reaction1 = 633644
    THEN t4.description
    WHEN a.reaction2 = 114861
    THEN t5.description
    WHEN a.reaction2 = 158053
    THEN t6.description
    WHEN a.reaction2 = 581679
    THEN t7.description
    WHEN a.reaction2 = 633644
    THEN t8.description
  END AS typical_symptoms
FROM allergies AS a
INNER JOIN concepts AS t1
  ON a.reaction1 = t1.code
INNER JOIN concepts AS t2
  ON a.reaction1 = t2.code
INNER JOIN concepts AS t3
  ON a.reaction1 = t3.code
INNER JOIN concepts AS t4
  ON a.reaction1 = t4.code
INNER JOIN concepts AS t5
  ON a.reaction2 = t5.code
INNER JOIN concepts AS t6
  ON a.reaction2 = t6.code
INNER JOIN concepts AS t7
  ON a.reaction2 = t7.code
INNER JOIN concepts AS t8
  ON a.reaction2 = t8.code
WHERE
  a.description = 'Shellfish (substance)';
```

question: What is the most promising procedure for a patient with Allergy to substance (finding)?

```sql
  a.code AS allergy_code,
  pr.description AS procedure_description,
  GROUP_CONCAT(DISTINCT t.description) AS type
FROM patients AS p
JOIN allergies AS a
  ON p.id = a.patient
JOIN procedures AS pr
  ON a.patient = pr.patient
JOIN types AS t
  ON a.code = t.code
WHERE
  a.description LIKE "%substance (finding)%"
GROUP BY
  p.first_name,
  a.patient,
  a.code
ORDER BY
  COUNT(*) DESC
LIMIT 1;
```

question: What is the successrate of medication Simvastatin 10 MG Oral Tablet?
answers:
```sql
SELECT
  m.code,
  m.description,
  COUNT(m.code) / CAST(COUNT(DISTINCT p.id) AS FLOAT) AS success_rate
FROM medications AS m
JOIN encounters AS e
  ON m.encounter = e.id
JOIN patients AS p
  ON e.patient = p.id
WHERE
  m.description LIKE '%Simvastatin 10 MG Oral Tablet%'
  AND (
    m.stop IS NULL OR DATE('now') BETWEEN DATE(m.start) AND DATE(m.stop)
  )
GROUP BY
  m.code,
  m.description;
```
